Awful!  What a difference in service from 3 years ago.  I think the ownership has changed.  Here's where they go wrong:
- The rude man with an attitude who writes out your ticket.  No people skills, condescending tone who  looks at people through the lens of racist stereotypes.
- They have adopted a policy of leaving you dissatisfied so you are forced to upgrade your washes.  When you upgrade your wash, you are still dissatisfied, because they imply that you get a detail job.
- They don't do the basics: not use air to get particles out of crevices and corners?  Not wipe down seats?  Not wipe mirrors?
I would seriously reconsider spending $25 because it's an assumption that you won't later have to ask them to redo things or do them yourself.
Just wasted 40 minutes of my time to hear them tell me they don't do things most $7.99 washes do so you are compelled to tip the laborers better.< /Review>

The Culver Auto Spa left my SUV sitting in the exit of the car wash tunnel, and as another car exited the car wash, it hit my vehicle several times, causing $1500 worth of damage to my vehicle.  The Culver Auto Spa refused to pay for the extent of the damage to the vehicle, offering me a settlement of less than 1/3 of that.  What's more, they told me this sort of thing happens all the time to them! I can't believe this place is still in business.  Don't go here if you value your car!

< user_name>

<date>1499303441415</date><Rate>2<//Rate>< Review>
As I drove away from Culver Auto Spa, I couldn't help but feel an overwhelming sense of disappointment. I got the Basic Car Wash for $16.99. I didn't expect a a perfect job, but I did expect my car vacuumed (which it was not - all they did was take out the car mats and shake the dirt off of them). I also expected the windows to be free of dirt and bugs (they were not - I had several bugs still stuck on the windshield after they were finished). The rear windshield was not even touched (I'll have to clean that myself). They did a good wax on my car though. Overall, disappointed. I've received far superior washes for far less (Irvine Auto Wash did a fantastic job on my car - a detailed hand wash for $7). There's a reason that Culver Auto Spa has a measly 2 star rating - they aren't very good at whay they do: washing cars. They have a great location, and that's what gets them business. If you have the time though (or if you care about getting a good job done on your vehicle), avoid this place and go somewhere else.<//Review>

First of all, the staff is beyond rude. When I told the guy who took my car that I just wanted a basic wash, he literally rolled his eyes at me. After I paid I decided to go across the street to get some starbucks because it looked like there were a lot of people waiting in front of me. When I got back, they were barely finishing drying my car so I asked the guy if they were done and he said yes so I asked if I could have my keys. He very angrily yelled at me "I need your reciept!". It was an honest mistake on my part, I never get my car done at places like this. So I pulled out mine and my boyfriends reciepts (he was getting his car done too) and before I could give him just mine he snatched both out of my hands and walked away. I called after him to tell him he took both but he just ignored me.
What happened next took this awful service to the next level. I went back to my apartment, which is a one minute drive away, expecting my boyfriend to be right behind me. He did not show up for 20 minutes. The workers parked cars all around him to block his car in and ignored him when he asked them if they could move one so he could get out. He then resorted to asking one of the car owners if he could move his car to get out and the guy literally told him to f*** off. So my boyfriend then found the manager and asked him to help out with the situation to which the manager simply replied "you shouldn't have made us wait for you" even though they were not even done with his car by the time we got back from across the street! And might I add that even if they did have to wait for us, they have separate parking spots for customers they are waiting on.
Basically, everyone working there is rude beyond belief (except for the cashier). And it is also true that the actual cleaning service they provide is extremely basic and not worthy of the cost. They don't even vacuum! You'd probably be happier just going to a gas station automatic car wash for the same cleaning service for less than half the price and you won't have to deal with being treated so poorly!< /Review>

< review>
Quick and easy spot to order food. Open at 10am and were quick to order and serve your dishes. Ordered the bum bo hue and came out to what I expected, mild spicy and robust in what I'd want in a hearty soup. The blood cubes absorbed the broth and it's a taste I would want to have every once in awhile when I'm in the area.</review>

<username>Jimmy Anh Truong< /username><date>1557195881702<//date><Rate>5<//Rate>< Review>
I found a newly opened restaurant on Yelp and decided to give it a try. It Located inside a strip mall with many shops surrounding it. It was right in the Korea district and closed to little Saigon. It was small but visible from the street. I liked the decorations and its looks. It was almost full House when we came in. There were tables set outside if you preferred. Inside it was cleaned and organized. The staffs were friendly , welcoming and helpful. We tried their specialty Bun rieu and Bun moc , they were delicious and yummy. They were very interacted with customers one on one to make sure their customer's  satisfactions. The noise was medium and better yet as they told us this was a family run restaurant. They even told us the foods were prepared and made by the family. That was good to hear and was proud of that. The broth was right on the money and tasted so good. Would be back to try out more their other specialty next time we are in town.</Review>

< user>
115178373811211723065< /user>
< user_name>
Hamilton Nguyen</user_name>
<date>1564460426540<//date>< rating>
5<//rating>
<text>When I sat down at the table, the first thing I noticed was they had mam tom (shrimp paste) in a jar on the table. As soon as I saw that, I had high hopes for this place because I knew that this place was going to be authentic.

I had the canh bun and the broth was very fragrant. The meats in the soup were very tender. The fish cakes nice and light, yet had a soft chew to them. The blood cubes had a great flavor without any of the funk to them. Just clean irony taste, which is rare to find. The noodles complemented the broth very well; it was nice and chewy and held on to the broth well. One thing that usually is overlooked is the fresh ground chili paste. It was fresh and very spicy and went so well with the soup.

I highly recommend this place if you want to try some authentic vietnamese noodle soups that isn't the typical pho you see everyday.

I will be back to try more of their menu.</text><pictures>None</pictures>< Response>
None</Response>

<username>Angel Wings</username>< text>
Had to find a place to service my Mini Cooper and found this one had good reviews on BOTH Yelp and Google.

From Day 1 Pete and his crew were very HELPFUL & HONEST.

They answered all my questions. I spoke to Paul and he told me what I could expect and gave me a cost estimate and timeframe. He worked with my work schedule.

The service went smoothly and they kept me up to date and answered questions via text. They let me know my tires were balding and was able to provide multiple (price tier - fancy vs. economy) fix options.

All work was completed in about 24 hours for my particular issues.

A few days later they checked in on me to see if everything was good. I let them know there was a service light that would not go off or was not reset (related). Pete himself came all the way down to my place and fixed it!!!

I like this place. They provided great service and work.

Price is fair/honest and competitive. Service makes it worth it.<//text>

They have no way of checking the status of the tires and that maybe they should be arriving in the next shipment for 10am or 12pm, same day.

They question the validity of my order and ask if I received confirmation about my tires being in stock when online services state they‚Äôre in stock and ready for pick up same day.

After two separate search attempts, the cashier has found the tires in the back.

For a company that offers online pay, you should inform and train your employees so that this doesn‚Äôt happen to other customers.

The work performed was mediocre at best. They returned the vehicle with tire sealant residue all over each tire. Soon after receiving the vehicle, I was driving on the freeway noticing that the one of the tires seemed unbalanced. The vehicle was shaking quite a bit and that was not happening before. After pulling off and checking the pressure of all 4 tires I found that they were inflated to well over 55PSI when the spec on the vehicle is 44F/48R.

The specifications for the tire pressure are listed on the inside of the drivers door well and I‚Äôm sure they have the same information in their database. Simple things like this make me question the competence of the service employees as well as managements minimal training. Guaranteed I will not be back to this location or any other Pep Boys locations. ‚úåÔ∏è</Review>

<rate>1<//rate>< review>
I came to this Pep Boys about 3 weeks ago on July 6(?) for a wheel alignment. Once my car was put on the rack I was immediately called back to the shop to be told that alignment was unable to be completed because my Sway Bar Link was broken and I had a bulging tire. The estimate to repair the parts and do the alignment was over $900. After looking at the estimate they were trying to make me repair my front end suspension! So thinking that I had no other options I saved the money to get the repairs, but I felt like I should get a second opinion before I committed to the repairs. I took my car to Navajo Repair in Apple Valley, CA and I was only charged $25 to repair a small part that had come loose and another $65 for the alignment.

In short, I spent 1/10th of what this store was trying to charge me! My car works great and drives smooth again like when we first got it. I'm writing this as a warning to other customers and in the hopes that someone from corporate sees this and does something to change the culture of this store. I work in sales so I understand the need to upsell products to customers but this is absurd. People do not have thousands to spend on unnecessary auto repairs and we come to you because we are unable to do it ourselves. I just hope that someone else doesn't go through the same experience I did.<//review>

<UserId.>113906810694732313430<//UserId.>< Text>
I WILL NEVER RECOMMEND THIS PEP BOYS TO ANYONE!!!!  In my opinion, this has to be the worst PEP BOYS ever. Traveling to many states while in the military this is the WORST Pep Boys ever. I have been using Pep Boys for years and have always received honesty and excellent customer service. My son moved from Orlando, FL  to California to continue his education. Before driving his car across country, we had brand new tires and other maintenance done on his car. We spent close to a $1000 just on the tires which are not even 7 months old. My son heard a loud noise coming from the back rear tire. So I told him to take the car to a Pep Boys in L.A. thinking that we would receive the same honest outcome. First of all, he was told that the tires are worn out unevenly, and that's where the noise was coming from. They gave him a price of over $400 for two back tires. Remember we had just purchased tires which I have the receipt. So I told my son while he was on the phone, to tell him that the tires are under warranty. The gentleman is going to tell him that the warranty doesn't go from state to state. Now I know that was a lie, cause I've always used Pep Boys. So I hung up the phone with my son to call the Pep Boys here in Orlando, just to find out that the warranty is nationwide. All this store in L.A. had to do was to get the store number and the invoice number which I got with one call. The information was under my son's telephone number. Would it have hurt them to go out their way to make a phone call? Oh, I forget the price was better without the warranty. So once they found out that there was a warranty, the price drops down to about $285.00. It doesn't stop there. Now they tell him that he has to purchase a lock for the wheel. As long as we have been using Pep Boys, we have never had to purchase a lock. Question? Why didn't they mention this when they gave us the first estimate? It doesn't stop there. The reason for him bringing the car is because of the loud noise on the rear tire. Well, the noise is still there. Unbelievable. So I called the store to speak to the manager by the name of Tony. I am explaining to him what took place, which is clear English. He continues to say what can he do for me. This place of business? I don't trust this company. In my opinion, they ripped us off and didn't even correct the problem. I asked for the next person in charge of him since he couldn't understand the issues. He says there is no one above him and that I would have to call 1-800 Pep Boys. I said once again, so there is no one above you, and he said no. I said, have you ever pulled up my son work order since I've been speaking. He says no because I didn't give him a chance. I shouldn't have had to give him a chance; he should have asked for the customer name. So I called my Pep Boys here in Orlando, just to find out that there is someone over him. I called 1-800-Pep Boys, and there is someone by the name of Victor over him. Once again it shows the integrity of this business. They should have found out that the tires were practically new before they came up with the bogus outcome. So now I am paying the Chevrolet Dealer to take care of the problem since this Pep Boys cannot take care of a 2013 Chevrolet Camaro.   The opinion that I can give is to stay clear of this business. I am now waiting to hear from the area manager. I will also be filing a BBB complaint.< /Text>
